meanings.definition: To produce more than (someone or something else)
meanings.sent1: The new factory outproduces the old one.
meanings.sent2: Our team consistently outproduces the competition.
meanings.sent3: The little ant outproduces the lazy grasshopper in gathering food.
meanings.sent4: Her determination outproduces any obstacle in her path.
meanings.sent5: The sun outproduces all other sources of light in the sky.

meanings.definition: To exceed in production or output
meanings.sent1: The efficient machine outproduces the manual labor.
meanings.sent2: During peak season, the farm outproduces its usual output.
meanings.sent3: The student's creativity outproduces his classmates in the art project.
meanings.sent4: The river outproduces the stream in its flow of water.
meanings.sent5: The athlete's stamina outproduces his opponents on the field.
